main event: An observer sighted a flashing light behind and above the trees in Shilow, Ohio on 1 Oct 1969.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 30 minutes., The object was observed in poor weather conditions., The observer had not seen a similar phenomenon before this instance., The report concluded there was insufficient data to analyze the event., The document was part of the Project Blue Book records.
sighted object: a flashing light in the sky
witness description: male, reported seeing the light alone
